HEADWORD: Caducibranchiate
<hw>Ca*du`ci*bran"chi*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>caducus</ets> falling (fr. <ets>cadere</ets> to fall) + E.
<ets>branchiate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>With temporary
gills: -- applied to those Amphibia in which the gills do not remain in
adult life.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

